# Skill ↔ repo coupling

Skills are orchestration runbooks. Shared behavior lives in the **repo**, not in other skills.

## Sources of truth

| Concern | Location |
|---------|----------|
| Shared policy (URL health, Notion IDs overview, cleanup) | `docs/shared/` |
| Notion constants / parsers / payloads | `scripts/lib/notion/` |
| Runtime paths | `scripts/lib/paths.ts` |
| npm entrypoints | `package.json` → `scripts/{source,scrape,fill,shared,auth}/` |
| Fill PII / resume | `.cursor/skills/application-filler/assets/` |

## When renaming or moving

1. Update `scripts/lib/paths.ts` and any writers that use those paths
2. Update `package.json` script entries
3. Update skill `protocol/repository-scripts-map.md` and `protocol/pipeline-commands.md`
4. Update `docs/shared/` if the shared contract changed
5. Update both skill indexes if a skill-local file moved

Skills must not depend on another skill’s folder. Point at `scripts/auth/`, `.auth/`, or `docs/shared/` instead.
